what were the open-door notes? The open-door notes were a type of note played on the trumpet. The player would hold the trumpet up to their mouth and then release it, making a sound like a door opening.

what were the open-door notes as regards the USA? The open-door notes were generally positive, with some expressing hope for a more positive future and others expressing disappointment in the current state of the United States.

what were the open-door notes as regards the USA and China? The open-door notes were generally positive, with both countries pledging to work together to improve trade and security. China also pledged to increase its investment in the USA, while the USA pledged to increase its investment in China.
